HEADWORD: Recumb
<hw>Re*cumb"</hw> <pr>(-k?m")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>recumbere</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> back + <ets>cumbere</ets> (in
comp.), akin to <ets>cubare</ets> to lie down.]</ety> <def>To lean; to
recline; to repose.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>J. Allen
(1761).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

